owrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unextonex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nextonex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 5:02:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=75.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Im level 39 and im getting tboots, Can i quad kite and h</span><hr size=1> Risk=Reward<br><br>I've yet to do any quading with bonds. Make sure to get the Staff of Temp Flux. I do all mine at full speed from the 4th view (3rd person). it makes it a little eaiser to avoid other mobs. <p>Nextonex Atomsmasher of PrexusAlways looking for a good AOE group- send me a tell!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspankda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spankda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 6:05:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=75.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Multi-Kiting</span><hr size=1> Quad-kiting is a myth pre-40.  Very rarely have I truly kited four mobs at once.  In fact, only once and then only partially successfully.<br><br>Of course, I'm only level 38.  You're ability to multi-kite is based on your mana pool and the relative mob level to you.  As the difference between my level and the highest mobs gets larger, my spells are resisted less and I have more mana.<br><br>You should start by dual-kiting.  You simply agro one mob, run with it behind you, and agro another.<br><br>I target one, click on my staff of temp flux, and run. I target another, click, run. <br><br>Then, make a big circle.  You'll figure out what's a good size.  Make two, three, four circles if need be.  Tighten the circles if you want.  <br><br>You've not wasted any mana at this point.  Your only timer is your SoW or T/Jboots at this point.  Take your time. <br><br>Be careful not to agro anything you don't want.  I've ended up with four in my snare when I intended to have two or three.  Sarnaks help each other out.<br><br>Be careful not to get too close.  I used to get hit all the time doing this.  I don't any more.<br><br>Then, run in a straight line.  For me, after one circle, I have a 98% chance of having my mobs together.<br><br>Run until you are out of spell range.  The staff of temp flux is good for this.<br><br>The mobs are literally on top of each other.  You may turn around and look and see three separate mobs all spread out.  This artificial vision is an artifact of lag.  You go aheand and snare.  All three will report the status.  Then, you'll see the three jump back on top of each other.<br><br>I've seen three knights walking as one.  It's a bizarre scene.  They are all literally at one spot together.<br><br>Don't let the lag fool you.  You don't even have to turn around.  Just stop, pause, snare.  Read the messages.<br><br>If you snare all two, three, or four, you're golden.  Simply run out of spell ranges, stop, pause, and cast Circle of Force.  Repeat.  You may wish to resnare one more time.<br><br>If the two or three mobs are each of different type, which is the case for me 80% of the time, then you will have to separate them out and finish them one at a time at the end.  The one with less HP will stop, snared and almost dead, while two others still are approaching you.<br><br>Pick a target and big DD it.  If you can still CoF more than one, do so.  Chance are, you'll have to single DD each to finish.  <br><br>On my last successful quad-kite, I had one cockatrice still undead, unsnared, barely alive, wandering around.  I sat to med.   The 'trice ran to the guards and I lost the kill.<br><br>You'll have to find your best strategy for resisted snares.  I've been able to re-round them all up and resnare, but at that point, I have less than enough mana to finish off the mobs.  In almost every case, I have to leave three or four unsnared and almost dead mobs chasing me around the zone while I am 100% OOM.<br><br>This scenario is very unsatisfying as you've wasted both the time you took to fight and the mana you need to med (and time) on nothing.  A few times doing this and you'll find another strategy soon.<br><br>So, I've begun taking three.  If two snare and one resists, I turn it into a single-kite with the resisted one.  I run straight away from the snared, recast snare on the resistant one until snared, then I kill it.  I then am at about two bubbles or less of mana.  No where near enough to finish the others.<br><br>Fortunately for me, the critters at The Overthere don't hunt me down.  Even if they did, they'd die coming through the guards to get me.<br><br>I have taken the resistant mob to the guards to let them kill it, go back to the snared ones, resnare, and kite kill.<br><br>Make sure you can outrun the mobs you chose when they are unsnared.  Never snare kite something that has the potential to be faster than you.  I do not recommend kiting a caster mob either. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 11:35:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=75.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Im level 39 and im getting tboots, Can i quad kite and h</span><hr size=1> Spankda - you have quading down pretty well, but you have yet to learn the single most important aspect, and its only becasue you are in the wrong zone...<br><br>ALWAYS quad mobs that are on the same faction.<br><br>This will fix your mob stopping problem. As long as there are 2 or more mobs of the same faction, they will NOT stop coming after you as they get low on health.<br><br>Quad kiting is not a myth pre-40, you just have to do it in the right place.<br><br>I will say it a 100 times if I have to. Wizards should live in Eastern Wastes 34-44. The area is wide open, easy to avoid unwanted adds, decent loot, insane exp.<br><br>***edit***<br>BTW - 1 trip to Kael arena, up to 4th shawl, a couple night quading dires and I am ally to Coldain, dubious to CoV. I am guessing I should be apprehensive after next Kael trip. <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 48th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br><i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Moordian Killbringer<br>Warrior of 25 Battle Scars</b><br><i>Dwarven LaMachine of Death</i><br><span style="font-size: 12px; font-famliy: arial">proud member of Infinity Watch - Terris-Thule server</span></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A> at: 6/20/01 10:06:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspankda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spankda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/01 2:26:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=75.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Same Faction</span><hr size=1> Cool.  I moved to Great Divide last night.<br><br>At The Overthere, I found three berzerkers in a ruin.  Cake. Right?<br><br>Wrong.  They were SoW'd.  Yeah.  I was surprised too.  I got a level 45 cleric to rez me.  Hey, half XP is better than zero.<br><br>Bored and ready to start working on my CoV faction, I moved to GD from seeing the postings here.<br><br>I did snare three Draekal Dire Wolves at once but a Giant noticed.  I just brought them all to the guards.  I did get two successfully, then I joined a giant killing group at the fort.  Heck.  Why not.<br><br>Interestingly, the group was mostly 40'ish folks with a 57 paladin in it working on his faction.  I did get XP.<br><br>I'm going to stay in GD primarily for faction, but I may go back to EW for XP as suggested.  There's nothing really flat and open about GD, but the guards are a nice thing to have.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubicrius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bicrius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/01 1:57:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=75.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://students.hamilton.edu/2002/bschulte/eqpics/bic_gin_sm.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Same Faction</span><hr size=1> If you want to quad kite and you're between levels 34 and 45, I just wrote this based on what I did. This should help you all. Good luck... <br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showMessage?topicID=78.topic">pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffe...D=78.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 BGCOLOR="#000000">   <TR>      <TD WIDTH=115>         <CENTER><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=29088" TARGET="_top"><IMG SRC="http://webster.ij.net/~eop/shots/b